20....., Nd7 ?!. 21 Bxb6, Nxb6. 22. bxc6, bxc6. 23, 0-0 leaves white with options. The played 20...., Bxc5 will follow with dxc5 and makes that pawn vulnerable there instead of being a strong center pawn. I think this will give black more options, also because the black rooks will work together quicker than white can bring in his second rook.
